	Romantic racing
 
	 Sydney, Dec. 31 (Reuters): Australian newlyweds kissing on the backseat of their hired car were unaware their chauffeur was street racing, until a police siren broke their romantic bliss and ended the race.
 
	The chauffeur, clocked at up to 130 kmph racing a young driver in a rental car, was arrested on the side of the road and the car confiscated.
 
	Its alleged that as the traffic light turned green both the (cars) accelerated harshly from the intersection and continued to travel at speed along the highway, police said.
 
	Newlyweds John and Laina Tauranga were escorted home in a police car. 
 
	Golden role
 
	 Los Angeles (AP): Her role in Atonement earned Saoirse Ronan a Golden Globe nomination, but she has not read the Ian McEwan novel the movie is based on. Ronan is only 13, and the book deals with sexual themes. Atonement is Ronans third film, but the Irish actress is already getting attentionfor her role as the young Briony Tallis. In 2008, she will appear with Bill Murray in the action-fantasy City of Ember and star as a con artist in Death Defying Acts alongside Catherine ZetaJones. 
                                                                           
